'''Kristin Elizabeth Cavallari''' (born January 5, 1987)<ref name=yahoobio>[http://tv.yahoo.com/kristin-cavallari/contributor/2175943/bio Yahoo! TV bio]</ref> is an American [[celebrity|television personality]] and [[actress]]. She is best known for her starring roles on the former [[MTV]] reality television programs ''[[Laguna Beach: The Real Orange County]]'' and its spin-off, ''[[The Hills]]''.
==Early life== Cavallari was born in [[Denver]], [[Colorado]], the second of two children of Judith Spies (nÃ©e Eifrig) and Dennis Cavallari.<ref name=swe>{{Cite news|last=Sims|first=Stephanie|coauthors=|title=Kristin Cavallari, Jay Cutler Escape To New York City After DUI|pages=|publisher=All Headline News|date=2010-09-13|url=http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7019888468|accessdate=2010-11-03}}</ref><ref name=stn>{{cite web|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|title=Descendants of Friedrich Wilhelm Eifrig|publisher=Genealogy.com|date=2009|url=http://familytreemaker.genealogy.com/users/e/i/f/Eric-W-Eifrig/GENE7-0004.html|accessdate=2010-11-03}}</ref>
When her mother divorced her father, her older brother, Mike, moved with their father to [[Laguna Beach, California]], while she moved with her mother to the village of [[Barrington, Illinois]], a suburb an hour northwest of [[Chicago]]. She attended Barrington Station Middle School, and graduated on to [[Barrington High School (Lake County, Illinois)|Barrington High School]]. After difficulties adjusting to a new life with a stepfather and stepbrother, Cavallari moved to California to live with her father. There, Cavallari was enrolled at [[Santa Margarita Catholic High School]] for her sophomore year. After she attended a Driver's Education course through [[Laguna Beach High School]], her father enrolled her in Laguna Beach High School.
==Career== ===Reality television=== Cavallari was in her [[High school junior|junior]] year of high school when the first season of ''[[Laguna Beach: The Real Orange County]]'' began production. At the time, she was involved in an on-and-off relationship with [[High school senior|senior]] [[Stephen Colletti]]. Cavallari's romance with Colletti caused a rivalry with another cast member, [[Lauren Conrad]]. The love triangle became one of the series' central plot lines. <ref name=yahoobio /> [[File:Kristin Cavallari @ Lincoln Center in New York City 02.jpg|thumb|125px|left|Cavallari at the [[Lincoln Center]] in 2010.]]
In May 2009 Cavallari confirmed that she would be joining the cast of the popular [[MTV]] reality series ''[[The Hills]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2009/05/its-official-kristin-cavallari-joins-the-hills.html|title=It's official: Kristin Cavallari joins 'The Hills'|date=2009-05-14|publisher=latimes.com|accessdate=2009-05-22}}</ref> She appeared in the mid-season finale that aired on May 31, 2009, and appeared as a regular in the remainder of the fifth season. She inked a deal with [[MTV]] to appear as a series regular throughout two more seasons of the series following the fifth.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodinsider.ew.com/2009/05/ew-exclusive-la.html|title=Exclusive interview: 'Laguna Beach' star Kristin Cavallari on joining 'The Hills'|last=Stack|first=Tim |date=2009-05-14|publisher=hollywoodinsider.ew.com|accessdate=2009-05-22}}</ref> The sixth and final season aired summer 2010.
Cavallari was on the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 13)|13th season]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' and partnered with two-time champion, [[Mark Ballas]]. Despite having high scores, Cavallari was the third to be eliminated, shocking the audience, judges, and fellow dancers alike. One of the judges, Len Goodman, commented that he expected to see Cavallari dancing in the final. The cumulative average of Cavallari's dances were higher than of contestants who had lasted twice as long as she did.
===Acting=== [[File:Kristin Cavallari at 2009 MTV VMA's.jpg|thumb|125px|right|Cavallari at the [[MTV Video Music Awards]] in 2009.]] After her stint on ''Laguna Beach'', Cavallari headed to Los Angeles and briefly attended the Loyola Marymount University. She signed on the [[UPN]] [[reality television]] series ''[[Get This Party Started]]'', which premiered February 7, 2006. The series was canceled after airing two episodes due to extremely low ratings. She guest starred on one episode of another [[UPN]] series, ''[[Veronica Mars]]''. She has appeared in numerous television roles such as ''[[CSI: NY]]'', ''[[Cane]]'' and ''[[Adventures in Hollyhood]]''. In 2006, she signed on as Crystal in the [[horror film|horror]] film ''[[Fingerprints (film)|Fingerprints]]''. She also played a small role in ''Wristcutters: A Love Story,'' an independent film, directed by Goran Dukic in 2006.
In 2008 she had a supporting role as Summer in ''[[Spring Breakdown]]'' alongside [[Amy Poehler]]. The film was released straight-to-DVD on June 2, 2009, and received mixed reviews. She also starred in the independent film ''[[Green Flash]]'' alongside [[Torrey DeVitto]]. In 2009 she starred in the independent American high school comedy film, ''[[Wild Cherry (2009 film)|Wild Cherry]]'', as Trish, which also starred [[Rumer Willis]]. She also starred in the straight-to-DVD film, ''[[National Lampoon's Van Wilder: Freshman Year]]'', as Kaitlyn. The film was released July 14, 2009, to mixed to negative reviews.
Sep 1, 2010 - Starred next to Jaron Lowenstein (Jaron and the Long Road to Love) in his Music Video, "Beautiful to Me."<ref>http://www.theboot.com/jaron-thats-beautiful-to-me-video-kristin-cavallari</ref>
==Activism== Cavallari has been involved in the "Until There's a Cure", [[public service advertising]] campaign, to raise awareness and funds for [[AIDS]] and [[HIV]] research and vaccine development.<ref>[http://www.utac.org/ads.shtml Until There's a Cure: Public Service Ads]</ref> In 2006 Cavallari appeared in ads for [[PETA]],<ref>[http://www.peta.org/feat/annualreview06/education.asp PETA Annual Review:2006]</ref> and has also appeared as a celebrity spokesperson for "We Are Ellis Island", a campaign for the restoration of [[Ellis Island]].<ref>[http://weareellisisland.com/stories/view/33 Save Ellis Island: Kristin Cavallari]</ref> In February 2009 she posed for the [[NOH8 Campaign]] in support of gay marriage.<ref>[http://www.noh8campaign.com/article/kristin-cavallari-mams-taylor-jennifer-gimenez Kristin Cavallari, Mams Taylor, & Jennifer Gimenez join the NO H8 Campaign]</ref>
In January 2010 she traveled to [[El Salvador]] to do [[charity (practice)|charity]] work. She told ''[[US Magazine]]'', "It really put everything into perspective and made me appreciate everything I have, seeing how happy and excited the kids were was the best feeling in the world". <ref>[http://www.usmagazine.com/healthylifestyle/news/kristin-cavallari-el-salvador-charity-work-was-incredible-experience-201052]</ref> In March 2011 Cavallari traveled to [[Kenya]], Africa, to do charity work with the [[non-profit organization]], One Kid One World. <ref>[http://www.givebackhollywood.com/2011/04/15/kristin-cavallari-travels-to-kenya-for-charity/]</ref>
==Personal life== Cavallari was engaged to [[Chicago Bears]] quarterback [[Jay Cutler (American football)|Jay Cutler]], but he called off their engagement in mid-July 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1224426,00.html | title= Cavallari & Brody Jenner Break Up| author=Ingrassia, Lisa | work=People.com}}</ref> In October 2011, it was reported that the couple got back together again. On November 30, 2011 Kristin tweeted, "This time its official..Jay and I are engaged again :)"
